column5: Fish slid out a bit deeper today. I had a couple of great guests out and we didn't catch huge numbers but got a few BIG fish. Rattle baits were king today.This was the biggest greenback I've seen this year.I even managed a nice one for my only fish today....can't answer the phone with me around.Been waiting all year for March on the ice...good way to kick things off.
Another awesome Manitoba winter eye jay !!!!!  Love the colors !!!!!! Cheers man !!!!!!!
Unreal Jay. Man I'd love to ice fish that body of water.
Very nice!!!!  .Only hear good things about fishing Manitoba!
I'd be freaked out if I caught a walleye that color in any of my area lakes haha. Great catches
Those fish despite their size still look quite edible.  Fantastic! Thanks for posting.
Wow, a couple of monsters right there, congrats.
wow that is a beast!!!  Cheers!
gotta be steroids in them there waters!
